  "texts": [
    "The entity representations are then fed into a multi-layer perceptron for training and ranking.Zhang et al. [515] proposed CAN, a context-aware FL approach based on GNN.",
    "CAN represents the failure context by constructing a program dependency graph, which shows how a set of statements interact with each other.",
    "Then, CAN utilizes GNNs to analyze and incorporate the context (e.g., the dependencies among the statements) into suspiciousness evaluation.Li et al. [516] proposed FixLocator, a DLFL approach that can locate faulty statements in one or multiple methods that need to be modified accordingly in the same fix.",
    "FixLocator utilizes dual-task learning with a method-level model and a statement-level model.",
    "Similarly, Dutta et al. [517] designed a hierarchical FL approach that uses two three-layer DNNs to first localize a function and then localize a statement.Yu et al."
  ],
